Task 1: Digital Literacy Infographic

I designed the infographic with Canva, which is a simple and user-friendly online tool for graphic design. My intention through this visual content was to educate students about the importance of digital literacy. Along with adding a definition of digital literacy, I also listed some very helpful digital. The point I wanted to get across with digital literacy is it simply not only being able to use technology but also being aware of its effects and making responsible choices. I also illustrated students' everyday tools like Google Docs, Canva, and GitHub to help them identify with these digital tools. Moreover, I used the infographic to stress major safety habits like creating strong passwords and steering clear of suspicious links. While working on this infographic, one aspect that really caught my attention was the power of simple visuals and concise points in conveying critical information effectively. On the other hand, a bit of challenge for me was picking the right design and layout that give a clean and neat look rather than an overcrowded one.
